    • enableFastWithdrawSwitch

      public com.binance4j.core.request.RequestExecutor<Void> enableFastWithdrawSwitch(FastWithdrawSwitchRequest req)
      Enables fast withdraw switch under your account.
      • >You need to enable "trade" option for the api key which requests this endpoint.
      • >When Fast Withdraw Switch is on, transferring funds to a Binance account will be done instantly. There is no on-chain transaction, no transaction ID and no withdrawal fee.
      Parameters:
      req - The custom request
      Returns:
      The executor permitting sync/async API call

    • transfer

      public com.binance4j.core.request.RequestExecutor<WalletTransferResponse> transfer(WalletTransferRequest req)
      Makse a universal transfer
      • You need to enable Permits Universal Transfer option for the api key which requests this endpoint.
      • fromSymbol must be sent when type are ISOLATEDMARGIN_MARGIN and ISOLATEDMARGIN_ISOLATEDMARGIN
      • toSymbol must be sent when type are MARGIN_ISOLATEDMARGIN and ISOLATEDMARGIN_ISOLATEDMARGIN
      Parameters:
      req - The custom request
      Returns:
      The executor permitting sync/async API call
      See Also:
      • Documentation

    • getTransferHistory

      public com.binance4j.core.request.RequestExecutor<WalletTransferHistory> getTransferHistory(WalletTransferHistoryRequest req)
      Fetches the user universal transfer history
      • fromSymbol must be sent when type are ISOLATEDMARGIN_MARGIN and ISOLATEDMARGIN_ISOLATEDMARGIN
      • toSymbol must be sent when type are MARGIN_ISOLATEDMARGIN and ISOLATEDMARGIN_ISOLATEDMARGIN
      • Support query within the last 6 months only
      • If startTime and endTime not sent, return records of the last 7 days by default
      Parameters:
      req - The custom request
      Returns:
      The executor permitting sync/async API call
      See Also:
      • Documentation
